The paper proposes a new algorithm for visual-inertial odometry for robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm uses a monocular camera and a 6-axis IMU, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the observability mismatch issue, which is related to control systems (cs.SY), and proposes a solution that does not require additional sensors, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
